Guide.title: Gartic Phone: how to play the game?
Guide.Content: Gartic Phone , popularized by Kameto on Twitch in recent days, is the succession of Skribble.io and Garlic.io. Developed by Onrizon Social Games, the creators of Garlic.io, this party-game allows you to play with friends from 4 players and up to 30, all on a web browser. You can therefore play this game on your PC or on your iOS or Android smartphone , the principle of which is the same as that of the Arabic telephone. We explain in this article how to play this new party-game sensation, and you can find this trick in our Gartic Phone guide .

Guide.title: HOW TO PLAY GARTIC PHONE?
Guide.Content: The principle of the game is the same as that of the Arabic telephone : the first player proposes a sentence, then the second player must draw to try to make the next player guess this sentence. Then the fourth player has to draw again to guess the sentence that the third player understood, and so on . At the end of the game, the players compare the last guessed sentence to the starting sentence , which should be as close as possible. In fact, the more players there are, the less similar the sentences will be!

Guide.title: Why you need a gartic phone
Guide.Content:
Gartic Phone takes you back to the good old days of gaming. Players can create powerful enemies and wield powerful weapons in an epic battle. There are over two hundred different monsters with unique characteristics to defeat. Beating the game will take a lot of effort. However, once you finish your battle, you can always grind to get the highest ranking in the world.

Its free to play and has zero advertisements. The game is also being developed in a way that players can get rewards in the form of in-game currency for joining a quest, interacting with other players and sharing content.
